dct_title_s: Roosevelt, Middlesex County, New Jersey : formerly Carteret
dct_description_sm: Includes key, key map, streets and specials index, and text. "221." "April 1908." The present town of Carteret was created as the borough of Roosevelt in 1906, from portions of Woodbridge Township. The name was changed back to Carteret in 1922.--cf. Wikipedia.
